definition: white/snowy/pure/bright/empty/blank/plain/clear/to make clear/in vain/gratuitous/free of charge/reactionary/anti-communist/funeral/to stare coldly/to write wrong character/to state/to explain/vernacular/spoken lines in opera

sentences.english: It is possible to trim off any blank area after printing.
sentences.chinese: 地图印刷完毕后，可将空白部分裁切掉。

sentences.english: I've filled in this form incorrectly. Can I have another blank?
sentences.chinese: 这张表我填错了，能否再给我一张空白表格？

sentences.english: C. back one year, put the year zero in the gap, and declare the disagreement solved.
sentences.chinese: 支持一年，投入年调零空白，并且宣称解决的分歧。

sentences.english: Unconsciously and unintentionally we fill up the gaps and supplement the dream-images.
sentences.chinese: 我们会不自觉地填补梦境中未被忆起的空白。

sentences.english: LX: As I said, during that entire time, my mind was blank.
sentences.chinese: 就像刚才我说的那样，那时我脑子一片空白。

sentences.english: Uncover the starting and ending points and start filling in the blanks one at a time.
sentences.chinese: 找到起始点，然后开始填补空白。

sentences.english: Point blank, it increases brain function. Barlean's makes a fish oil foam called Omega Swirl that tastes like candy.
sentences.chinese: 它能够激发空白点，提高脑功能。

sentences.english: I have something very unique to discuss with readers- the spirituality of work.
sentences.chinese: 很少友人谈论这个，因此我知道我填补了这个空白。

sentences.english: Any value may be assigned to the blank identifier.
sentences.chinese: 任何值都可以为空白标识符赋值。

sentences.english: We will replace this simple do-nothing application with the code in Listing 2, which does a whole lot.
sentences.chinese: 下面我会使用列表2中的代码来代替这个空白标签。

sentences.english: The utility model fills the blank of the special tank car for transporting the bulk dry-mixed mortar in China.
sentences.chinese: 填补了国内干混砂浆无散装运输专用罐车的空白。

sentences.english: Replace sequences of white-space within the string with a single space.
sentences.chinese: 在字符串内使用单空格替换连续的空白。

sentences.english: To fill the gap left by what Gehlen called instinctual deprivation. people create social frameworks.
sentences.chinese: 为了填补留下的空白什么盖伦所谓本能剥夺。

sentences.english: He said Washington "will not provide a blank check."
sentences.chinese: 他说，华盛顿“不会给他们一张空白支票”。

sentences.english: He legislates only between gaps. He fills the open spaces in the law.
sentences.chinese: 他只是在空白处立法，他填补着法律中的空缺地带。

sentences.english: But the study about leaf color genes engineering is almost vacancy.
sentences.chinese: 关于叶色基因工程则几乎是个空白。

definition: to fill a gap/to fill in a blank (on a form)/to overcome a deficiency
to break new ground (for agriculture)/to open up (a new seam)/to develop (border regions)/fig. to open up (new horizons)
